10px;">
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Shelf charter</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The cheapest way to get into the banking busin=
ess might be to buy a failed bank. When the US Federal Deposit Insurance Co=
rp. takes over a failed bank, it tries to find a buyer, and buying a bank f=
rom the FDIC has some attractive features. For one thing, you get a bank, w=
ith a brand name and customer relationships and branches and stuff; buildin=
g all of that from scratch would take you a lot of time and money. You get =
it cheap, probably, because it failed. And, critically, you don=E2=80=99t b=
uy the=C2=A0<em>whole=C2=A0</em>bank; you get to pick and choose what you w=
ant. You take over the failed bank=E2=80=99s customer deposits, but you can=
 avoid many of its other liabilities (long-term debt, lawsuits, etc.), maki=
ng it a fairly clean thing to buy. And you can buy most of the bank=E2=80=
=99s assets, but if it has any particularly hairy assets that you don=E2=80=
=99t want, you probably leave those with the FDIC.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is one problem with this approach, thoug=
h, which is that the FDIC won=E2=80=99t sell you a failed bank=C2=A0<em>unl=
ess you are already a bank</em>. This is the flip side of the good things i=
n the previous paragraph: If you buy a failed bank from the FDIC, you are n=
ot actually=C2=A0<em>buying the bank</em>, taking over the entire corporate=
 entity with its bank charter.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote=
-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !impo=
rtant; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0Instead, you are buying some of its assets and assuming some of i=
ts liabilities, including particularly deposits: The trade with the FDIC is=
 that you agree to be liable for $X of the bank=E2=80=99s deposits, you agr=
ee to pay the FDIC $Y=C2=A0for the assets you want, and the FDIC credits th=
e $X of assumed liabilities against the $Y purchase price.<a class=3D"footn=
ote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: n=
one !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bor=
der-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important=
; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But only a bank can issue bank deposits; that=
=E2=80=99s the point of a banking charter. So if=C2=A0<em>I=C2=A0</em>wante=
d to take over a failed bank, and I showed up at the FDIC and said =E2=80=
=9Clook, give me all of that bank=E2=80=99s assets, and I=E2=80=99ll be goo=
d for its deposits =E2=80=94=C2=A0if any depositors want their money back, =
they can come to me and I=E2=80=99ll get out my wallet,=E2=80=9D the FDIC w=
ould say no. Only a bank, with a banking charter, that meets capital and re=
gulatory requirements, is going to be allowed to take over the deposits.</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And so I guess one good way to get into the ba=
nking business is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Get yourself a bank charter.</li>=09<=
li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Wait.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5=
px;">When a bank fails, buy it.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/34672373.259366/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvNDgxZTY5=
MDEtYTA4NS00MzRkLWI5MmUtZjRhNzZkZmJlZDY0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB00eeb5cd"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;">Financial Times reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Porticoes Capital will seek to take over banks=
 closed by the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation, the US regulator, acc=
ording to an official filing. The firm=E2=80=99s sponsors aim to attract hu=
ndreds of millions of dollars from investors. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The FDIC takes over US lenders when they fail =
and brokers deals to sell what remains. The agency typically likes to sell =
to other regulated banks so the loans and customers of collapsed lenders re=
main under the eye of regulators. The result has been that private equity f=
irms and other outside investment groups are largely locked out of the bidd=
ing.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Porticoes won approval late last year from the=
 Office of the Comptroller of the Currency to buy banks closed by the FDIC.=
 Its so-called shelf charter is a workaround to traditional curbs on privat=
e investors. [Founder Leslie] Lieberman=E2=80=99s group was approved to run=
 a bank holding company once Porticoes actually buys a bank. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">More banks would need to fail for Porticoes to=
 be able to use money it has raised =E2=80=94 and the list of potential tar=
gets is slim.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Despite the turmoil of early 2023, only five b=
anks failed last year and all were resold within weeks.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yeah, but it doesn=E2=80=99t hurt right? It is=
 a little unclear to me whether Porticoes has raised, or is planning to rai=
se,=C2=A0much committed capital. I don=E2=80=99t see why you=E2=80=99d need=
 to lock up hundreds of millions of dollars to just wait for a bank to fail=
. The value here is not the=C2=A0<em>money</em>, it=E2=80=99s the charter. =
Next time a bank fails, you go to private equity firms and say =E2=80=9Chey=
, do you want to buy that failed bank? Well you can=E2=80=99=E2=80=8B=E2=80=
=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8B=E2=80=8Bt. But if you give us the money, we can buy i=
t for you.=E2=80=9D It=E2=80=99s a good regulatory service.</p>
