<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">No, wrong, this might be <a href=3D"https://li=
nk.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34672373.259366/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21=
iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2ZlYXR1cmVzLzIwMjQtMDMtMTMvaXMtanN4LXNhZmUtY29tcGV0aXRvcn=
Mtd2FudC1mYWEtdG8ta2lsbC10cmF2ZWwtaGFjay1mb3Itc2VjdXJpdHktcmlza3M_Y21waWQ9Q=
kJEMDMxMzI0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0=
ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwMzEzJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a3=
19a23cB544ed4b8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_=
blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bo=
ttom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; =
background-color: #ccc;">my favorite business origin story of all time</a>:=
</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Wilcox got the idea for the service in what=E2=
=80=99s possibly the least glamorous business origin story of all time. Com=
bing through US Federal Aviation Administration regulations, he learned tha=
t while scheduled flights with more than nine seats have to meet onerous sa=
fety and security requirements, on-demand public charters have separate, le=
ss stringent rules. Though, they can=E2=80=99t specify flight times or citi=
es or sell single seats.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">To get around that, Wilcox decided to create t=
wo companies that would work together: One would make a flight schedule and=
 sell tickets, and a second would fly the aircraft on specified routes at s=
et times and dates. In reality, though, it=E2=80=99s one entity working beh=
ind the scenes.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CI spent months without sleep, just lo=
oking at all the rules, looking for ways why it couldn=E2=80=99t be done,=
=E2=80=9D he said on a clear February day in a hangar at Dallas Love Field.=
 =E2=80=9CEvery single person we talked to said, =E2=80=98No, you can=E2=80=
=99t do it.=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D Then US regulators signed off on his idea. =
=E2=80=9CSo we did it.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That is from a Bloomberg <a href=3D"https://li=
nk.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34672373.259366/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21=
iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2ZlYXR1cmVzLzIwMjQtMDMtMTMvaXMtanN4LXNhZmUtY29tcGV0aXRvcn=
Mtd2FudC1mYWEtdG8ta2lsbC10cmF2ZWwtaGFjay1mb3Itc2VjdXJpdHktcmlza3M_Y21waWQ9Q=
kJEMDMxMzI0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0=
ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwMzEzJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a3=
19a23cC544ed4b8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_=
blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bo=
ttom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; =
background-color: #ccc;">story about JSX</a>, a charter airline that Alex W=
ilcox started after sleepless nights of reading FAA regulations. He read an=
d read and read the rules until he found an arbitrage.<a class=3D"footnote-=
index" href=3D"#footnote-3" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; di=
splay: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a> If you have an airline that sells and operates scheduled flights, you =
are subject to high and expensive safety standards. But if you=C2=A0<em>div=
ide=C2=A0</em>that airline into two bits, one that operates flights and ano=
ther that serves as a front end to set schedules and sell tickets, each bit=
 is subject to lower standards. If the two bits are owned by the same corpo=
rate entity and coordinate together, then the result is something that look=
s like a single normal airline=C2=A0<em>to customers</em>, but looks like t=
wo separate less-regulated entities=C2=A0<em>to regulators</em>.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I guess this is not technically a=C2=A0<em>fin=
ance=C2=A0</em>story, but half of what I write about has the form =E2=80=9C=
if you do Thing X it gets Regulatory Treatment Y, but if you divide it into=
 Things X1 and X2, the combination is the same as Thing X but gets better R=
egulatory Treatment Z.=E2=80=9D We have talked about <a href=3D"https://lin=
k.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34672373.259366/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21i=
ZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDMtMTEvY2FzaC1hZHZhbmNlLWxvb2tzLWE=
tbG90LWxpa2UtYS1sb2FuP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAzMTMyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW=
1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDMxMyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249b=
W9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa8a5768e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" ite=
mscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decora=
tion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0000=
00; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">treating loans as =
purchases</a>, about derivatives to get around <a href=3D"https://link.mail=
