"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">also wrote about Avid last =
week</a>, and he made another point:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Right now, it's suddenly gotten mu=
ch easier to do this at scale: you can unleash LLMs on indenture agreements=
, and try to find edge cases that the company didn't think of or notice. Th=
ese will all be technicalities in practice; in the Avid case, if the restri=
ction had been a big deal to the note owner, they probably would have notic=
ed right away. But, perhaps coincidentally, they only noticed after the new=
ly-widespread availability of tools that can trawl through vast amounts of =
text to extract useful information.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I don=E2=80=99t know if the explanation for th=
e Avid situation is really =E2=80=9Csome hedge fund used an artificial inte=
lligence=C2=A0large language model to look through convertible bond indentu=
res to find profitable mistakes=E2=80=9D; as a former converts structurer m=
yself, I would like to think that some former converts structurer found thi=
s trade using general market knowledge and connoisseurship. But the larger =
point is right: An LLM probably can read the boring documents for you and s=
pot the issues. And if =E2=80=9Cfind profitable mistakes in bond indentures=
=E2=80=9D is a useful thing to ask your LLM to do, then maybe so is =E2=80=
=9Cfind profitable loopholes in aviation regulations and tell me what busin=
esses to start to exploit them.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway the Bloomberg JSX story goes on:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">All that growth might now be the company=E2=80=
=99s undoing.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The FAA says its review of rules for public ch=
arter carriers like JSX came =E2=80=9Cin light of recent high-volume operat=
ions=E2=80=9D that =E2=80=9Cappear to be offered to the public as essential=
ly indistinguishable from=E2=80=9D commercial carriers. The =E2=80=9Csize, =
scope, frequency and complexity=E2=80=9D of public charter operations like =
JSX has =E2=80=9Cgrown significantly over the past 10 years,=E2=80=9D the a=
gency wrote in an August=C2=A0filing.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Ah well. Nothing lasts forever; on to the next=
 business model.</p>
