<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One more good business model. Learn a real thi=
ng about the world; learn to predict weather or something. Then hope that t=
hat thing gets ingested into the financial system, so that instead of predi=
cting weather as one of many inputs into some difficult complicated physica=
l business like farming or homebuilding or airline operations, you can just=
 trade concentrated weather derivatives on a computer and get rich directly=
 off your weather-predicting abilities. Here=E2=80=99s a <a href=3D"https:/=
/link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34672373.259366/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxv=
b21iZXJnLmNvbS9mZWF0dXJlcy8yMDI0LWNhdGFzdHJvcGhlLWJvbmRzLWZlcm1hdC8_Y21waWQ=
9QkJEMDMxMzI0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZX=
R0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwMzEzJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524=
a319a23cB9ea8c583" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D=
"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid=
; background-color: #ccc;">Bloomberg profile of John Seo</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Seo, a 57-year-old hedge fund manager in south=
ern Connecticut, is the reason why millions of people from New Zealand to C=
hile have financial protection against natural disasters. His fund, Fermat =
Capital Management, owns the world=E2=80=99s biggest collection of catastro=
phe bonds =E2=80=94 complex financial instruments that insurers issue to co=
ver risks they can=E2=80=99t handle.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Fermat is an oddity in the hedge fund world. I=
ts modest office, in the affluent town of Westport, sits in a former post o=
ffice across from an auto-repair shop. There are meteorology journals in th=
e reception area and equations scrawled on a whiteboard. Investment decisio=
ns are guided by complicated weather-risk computer models powered by large =
servers that whirr ceaselessly behind a glass window. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Investing in cat bonds was the most profitable=
 hedge fund strategy of 2023. Fermat delivered a 20% return, beating the av=
erage 8% achieved by hedge funds as a whole. While other cat bond funds did=
 well too, Fermat's $10 billion portfolio =E2=80=94 capturing a quarter of =
the market =E2=80=94 made it by far the most prolific investor to take adva=
ntage of a bumper year. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Seo, who has a PhD in biophysics from Harvard =
University, founded Fermat in 2001 with his brother Nelson, an economics gr=
aduate from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology. In a room above Seo=
=E2=80=99s garage, the two built a science-based model to weigh the probabi=
lity of a natural disaster against the returns of a cat bond. They named th=
e fund after Pierre de Fermat, a French mathematician who helped lay the fo=
undation for probability theory.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Quantitative financial firms regularly use phy=
sical=C2=A0models as <em>metaphors=C2=A0</em>for financial markets =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0stocks move sort of like particles in <a href=3D"https://link.mail=
.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34672373.259366/aHR0cHM6Ly9lbi53aWtpcGVkaWEub3=
JnL3dpa2kvQnJvd25pYW5fbW90aW9u/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB68de3ecc" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
 Brownian motion</a>, and this profile has a discussion of =E2=80=9Cone of =
Fermat=E2=80=99s strategies=E2=80=9D that is =E2=80=9Cinspired by the laws =
of physics that govern how airplanes fly=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94 but of course i=
f you can just use physical models to=C2=A0<em>actually predict the weather=
=C2=A0</em>that probably helps you trade catastrophic weather risk.</p>
